{
  "stem": "19690.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 76.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We jumped out of bed and when we got to the hallway, there were four SS standing there fully armed, bayonets mounted-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] --taking roll of who was in the house.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] They then ordered all of us to be ready by eight o'clock, to pack, take three days' provisions with us, and take clothes as needed.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "My grandparents were in rather precarious health, and my mother and everybody else appealed that they wouldn't have to go.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Later that morning, a supervisor came who was the [INAUDIBLE], the mayor of the town, and he guaranteed that my grandparents would not have to go and that they would be under his protective custody.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the pressure was off a little bit.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Cooking things to take was a little bit difficult at four or five o'clock in the morning, you didn't expect it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One thing that we always did was my grandmother and my mother always preserved eggs.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This is a method of taking fresh eggs in the spring when they're cheap and putting them in water with a calcium solution, and that keeps the eggs fresh and they were used mostly for cooking.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They wouldn't have-- in cooking, you wouldn't notice that little slightly off taste.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So my mother started cooking off boiled-- hard boiled eggs, probably three dozen.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I remember we had a little suitcase that was my little children's suitcase that she filled with hard boiled eggs.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So then a little bit later in the morning, probably about six, she said, we have no-- no bread and several other things.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So they permitted me and my cousin to go to the bakery and pick up bread and to the grocery store and pick up whatever things we needed.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
